Exception
- is an event can cause program termination

Errors: 2 type
1. Syntax error: ex - missing comma, , curly braces while writing program
2. Logic error : the program is executed but output we expect is not correct
----->
- If you have a syntax error, you can NOT execute program
- If you have a logic error, you STILL can execute program but result is not

How exception work
- In a program, developer/user provide invalid input in one statement -> Next statement
will return exception -> The program has forced pause

Exception types:
1. Checked exception: identified by Java compiler
2. Unchecked exception: NOT identified by Java compiler - MORE WORK

Using exception in practical code
- When exception happens, return warning or action

